color=#333399>(6/3/02 9:01:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27485.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lag999/rtfm.txt width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Upcoming changes to pets</span><hr size=1> Imaginos9 says:  <b><i>A Dire Charmed pet will take 50% if it does more damage then all party members combined.<br>
<br>
A Dire Charmed pet will take a scaling percent from 0% to 50% depending on how much damage it does compared to the rest of the party.</b></i><br>
<br>
My point exactly -- that's not the way pets used to work.<br>
<br>
It used to be that a pet would take no experience if it did not outdamage the group, and if it did outdamage the group, it would take a proportional share based on the level of the owner.<br>
<br>
If I was in a group of 6 equally-leveled players and my pet did more than 50% of the damage, it would take about 14% of the experience -- maximum.  If the pet did not do more than 50% of the damage, it would take 0% of the experience.<br>
<br>
From the way I read this message, a charmed pet will never take 0% any more, even if the group outdamages it.  Nerf #1.  And, it will take up to <b>75%</b> of the experience from the group (as opposed to 14%).  Nerf #2.<br>
<br>
Next, the message lies to us:<br>
<br>
<b>In most situations, dire charmed pets will take less experience than they did previously.</b><br>
<br>
Since my pet previously took 0% almost every time, I don't see how this change will make it take less experience.  On the contrary, it sounds like it will <b>ALWAYS</b> take more experience than before, based on some vague, unspecified range.  Will it range from 0% to 75% (the only other number mentioned there)?  If so, that would be massive XP nerf to charm.  Nerf #3, if you will. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uh0gfather.showPublicProfile?language=EN>H0gfather</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333399>(6/4/02 8:36:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27485.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Upcoming changes to pets</span><hr size=1> While its hard to say without the numbers, here's the way I see it (pet exp theft changes).<br>
<br>
Pet SOLO kill = 75% hit for all pets.<br>
<br>
Summoned / charmed pet with help = 0%<br>
<br>
Dire Charm pet = <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> at maximum a full share</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, or 14% in a full group. This occurs when the pet delivers more than 50% of the damage.<br>
<br>
Now this is where I completely speculate, the scale where the pet deals under 50% of the damage could be anything really. Even if it is a 1:1 scale, in a usual group of 3-4 damage dealers the pet alone will probably be doing as well as any of them, so it will be delivering 20-25% of the damage for the kill, which if its a linear scale would be about a 2-4% total hit (a quarter to a fifth of 14 or thereabouts).<br>
<br>
I personally suspect that as the pets portion of the damage decreases the exp hit will decrease in a non-linear fashion.<br>
<br>
Now that said, given how powerful and useful a DC pet is, I personally will still want one there with us, 2-4% exp hit or not. The only problem I can see for druids and other DC players is that you might encounter the same mentality that mages did when pet exp theft was brought up, in that eediots will assume that DC pet = massive exp loss, despite what the fact of the matter is.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the well wishes tho, hopefully they have something nice in the pipe for you guys. Last time Rich dropped by he mentioned they will be playing with pets then leaving the INT casters alone for a hwile and look at priests ... so hopefully the wait won't be toooo long for you all! <p><B><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26251">Hogfather</A></b><P>
